  71,764 for the member of staff to remain entitled to the household
  allowance. (ECB Conditions of Employment, p.9.)  2. What to include
  and how to calculate it: Add together, for the calendar year
  preceding the year in respect of which eligibility is assessed, the
  spouse’s income from employment or self‑employment (freelance
  consulting counts as self‑employment) and any pension and
  income‑replacement payments; measure amounts before tax and before
  deduction of social security contributions. Do not include
  investment income or capital gains. (ECB Staff Rules, p.63; ECB
  Conditions of Employment, p.9.)  3. Comparison and result: Compare
  the total calculated as above with EUR 71,764. If the total is
  greater than EUR 71,764, the household allowance is not payable to
  the member of staff; if it is equal to or below EUR 71,764,
  entitlement may continue. (ECB Conditions of Employment, p.9; ECB
