Average Metric: 13.00 / 15 (86.7%):  88%|████████▊ | 14/16 [01:26<00:07,  3.74s/it]Average Metric: 13.00 / 15 (86.7%):  94%|█████████▍| 15/16 [01:26<00:05,  5.59s/it]Question: I'm approaching the end of my ECB contract and have been notified that
  a cooling-off period applies, which prevents me from taking up the
  new role I had lined up. What financial support is available during
  that period?
Example answer: Certain staff intending to engage in a new occupational activity after
  the end of their ECB employment must refrain, for a specified
  cooling-off period, from any activity that could conflict with the
  ECB's interests. Staff who are prohibited as a result of that
  cooling-off period from undertaking a specific activity and who
  cannot find a suitable alternative and are consequently unemployed
  are entitled, for the duration of the prohibition, to a special
  monthly allowance of 80% of the last basic salary for the first year
  and 60% for the year thereafter, household and child allowances,
  continued cover under the ECB health, long-term care and accident
  insurance (subject to contributions), an education allowance capped
  at EUR 393 per month (or EUR 764 for certified imperative
  educational needs), and accrual of pensionable service. (ECB
  Conditions of Employment, pages 3, 18–19)
Predicted answer: Entitlement — If a cooling‑off period prevents you from taking up an
  occupational activity and you are consequently unemployed, you are
  entitled to unemployment‑related financial support for the duration
  of the prohibition and while you remain unemployed, under the
  conditions laid down in the Staff Rules. Key elements:   - Monthly
  unemployment allowance: 60% of your last basic salary for six
  months; then 30% of your last basic salary for the subsequent six
  months, with possible additional months related to years of service
  and age.   - Household and child allowances continue to be payable.
  - Continued insurance cover: continued cover under ECB health
  insurance, long‑term care insurance and accident insurance, subject
  to payment of the relevant contributions.   - Education allowance:
  reimbursement up to EUR 393 per month (increased to EUR 764 per
  month for children with certified, imperative educational needs);
  payable only until the end of the academic year in which you become
  unemployed and subject to the usual conditions.   - One‑off payment:
  where applicable, a one‑off payment equal to one month’s salary at
  Band A, step 1 for each full year of service completed (payable on
  evidence of registration as unemployed and seeking work), subject to
  a minimum of the equivalent of three months’ Band A, step 1 and a
  maximum of the equivalent of twelve months’ Band A, step 1.
  Conditions/authority — Entitlement applies while the prohibition
  applies and you remain unemployed; detailed conditions are laid down
  in the Staff Rules and the cooling‑off regime (including possible
  waivers) is governed by the Staff Rules/Executive Board processes.
  (ECB Conditions of Employment, pp.17–18; ECB Staff Rules, p.9)
Rationale: Recall score: 0.4, sources score: 1.0, length score: 0.52.
Score: 0.6

