Question: I'd like to telework from a country outside the EU for a couple of
  weeks. What is the annual cap on this, and within that period, what
  is the maximum I can do consecutively?
Example answer: Out of the maximum 90 working days per calendar year of teleworking
  from a location within the Union, members of staff may telework from
  a location outside the Union for up to 20 working days per calendar
  year. In addition, teleworking shall not exceed a maximum of 10
  consecutive working days, a limit that applies both within and
  across calendar months and also where teleworking is combined with
  leave, since leave does not interrupt the consecutiveness. (ECB
  Staff Rules, pages 83–84)
