  applies within and across calendar months and also where teleworking
  is combined with leave). (ECB Staff Rules, Article 5.1bis.4 and
  consecutive‑days provision, p.84; p.87).  3. Additional practical
  limits and definitions: “Working day” means eight hours for
  full‑time staff (pro‑rated for part‑time); teleworking from outside
  the Union is only permitted from a country compatible with the ECB’s
  IT and confidentiality requirements and staff remain solely
